# ============================================================
# 3.1  Download Price Data
# ============================================================

# Tickers to download
yf_tickers = [h['yf_ticker'] for h in holdings.values()]
benchmark_tickers = ['SPY', 'ACWI']  # S&P 500 & MSCI ACWI
all_tickers = yf_tickers + benchmark_tickers

# Date range: 2 years
end_date = datetime.now()
start_date = end_date - timedelta(days=2*365)

print(f"Downloading data from {start_date.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} to {end_date.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
print(f"Tickers: {len(all_tickers)}")
print()

# Download all data
raw_data = yf.download(all_tickers, start=start_date, end=end_date, auto_adjust=True, progress=True)

# Extract Close prices
if isinstance(raw_data.columns, pd.MultiIndex):
    prices = raw_data['Close'].copy()
else:
    prices = raw_data[['Close']].copy()

# Check for failed downloads
available = prices.columns[prices.notna().sum() > 10].tolist()
failed = [t for t in all_tickers if t not in available]
if failed:
    print(f"\n Failed/insufficient data for: {failed}")
    print("These will be excluded from analysis.")

# Keep only valid tickers
prices = prices[available].copy()

# Forward fill then backfill small gaps
prices = prices.ffill().bfill()

# Drop any remaining rows with all NaN
prices = prices.dropna(how='all')

print(f"\n Successfully loaded {len([t for t in available if t not in benchmark_tickers])} holdings + {len([t for t in available if t in benchmark_tickers])} benchmarks")
print(f"Date range: {prices.index[0].strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} to {prices.index[-1].strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
print(f"Trading days: {len(prices)}")

# ============================================================
# 3.2  Compute Returns
# ============================================================

# Daily returns
returns = prices.pct_change().dropna()

# Separate portfolio tickers from benchmarks
port_tickers = [t for t in available if t not in benchmark_tickers]

# Build weight vector (aligned with available tickers, normalised)
name_to_yf = {k: v['yf_ticker'] for k, v in holdings.items()}
yf_to_weight = {}
for name, info in holdings.items():
    yf_to_weight[info['yf_ticker']] = info['weight']

weights_series = pd.Series({t: yf_to_weight.get(t, 0) for t in port_tickers})
weights_series = weights_series / weights_series.sum()  # normalise

# Portfolio daily returns (weighted)
port_returns = (returns[port_tickers] * weights_series).sum(axis=1)
port_returns.name = 'Portfolio'

# Benchmark returns
bench_returns = {}
for b in benchmark_tickers:
    if b in returns.columns:
        bench_returns[b] = returns[b]

# Combined returns for comparison
combined_returns = pd.DataFrame({'Portfolio': port_returns})
for b, r in bench_returns.items():
    combined_returns[b] = r
combined_returns = combined_returns.dropna()

# Cumulative returns
cum_returns = (1 + combined_returns).cumprod() - 1

print(" Returns computed")
print(f"Portfolio daily return mean: {port_returns.mean()*252:.2%} (annualised)")
print(f"Portfolio daily return std:  {port_returns.std()*np.sqrt(252):.2%} (annualised)")

6. Key Portfolio Metrics & Ratios

Comprehensive risk-return metrics computed on daily data, annualised where appropriate.

In[10]:
# ============================================================
# 6.1  Performance Metrics Table
# ============================================================

def compute_metrics(returns_series, rf_annual=0.045):
    """Compute comprehensive portfolio metrics."""
    rf_daily = (1 + rf_annual) ** (1/252) - 1
    excess = returns_series - rf_daily
    
    ann_ret = returns_series.mean() * 252
    ann_vol = returns_series.std() * np.sqrt(252)
    sharpe = excess.mean() / returns_series.std() * np.sqrt(252) if returns_series.std() > 0 else 0
    
    # Sortino (downside deviation)
    downside = returns_series[returns_series < 0]
    downside_std = downside.std() * np.sqrt(252)
    sortino = (ann_ret - rf_annual) / downside_std if downside_std > 0 else 0
    
    # Max Drawdown
    cum = (1 + returns_series).cumprod()
    running_max = cum.cummax()
    drawdowns = (cum - running_max) / running_max
    max_dd = drawdowns.min()
    
    # Calmar Ratio
    calmar = ann_ret / abs(max_dd) if max_dd != 0 else 0
    
    # VaR & CVaR (95%)
    var_95 = np.percentile(returns_series, 5)
    cvar_95 = returns_series[returns_series <= var_95].mean()
    
    # Win rate
    win_rate = (returns_series > 0).sum() / len(returns_series)
    
    # Skewness & Kurtosis
    skew = returns_series.skew()
    kurt = returns_series.kurtosis()
    
    # Best / Worst day
    best_day = returns_series.max()
    worst_day = returns_series.min()
    
    # Gain-to-Pain ratio
    gain_to_pain = returns_series.sum() / abs(returns_series[returns_series < 0].sum()) if abs(returns_series[returns_series < 0].sum()) > 0 else 0
    
    return {
        'Annual Return': f'{ann_ret:.2%}',
        'Annual Volatility': f'{ann_vol:.2%}',
        'Sharpe Ratio (rf=4.5%)': f'{sharpe:.3f}',
        'Sortino Ratio': f'{sortino:.3f}',
        'Calmar Ratio': f'{calmar:.3f}',
        'Max Drawdown': f'{max_dd:.2%}',
        'VaR (95% daily)': f'{var_95:.2%}',
        'CVaR (95% daily)': f'{cvar_95:.2%}',
        'Win Rate (daily)': f'{win_rate:.2%}',
        'Best Day': f'{best_day:.2%}',
        'Worst Day': f'{worst_day:.2%}',
        'Skewness': f'{skew:.3f}',
        'Excess Kurtosis': f'{kurt:.3f}',
        'Gain/Pain Ratio': f'{gain_to_pain:.3f}',
    }

# Compute for all
metrics_dict = {}
metrics_dict['Portfolio'] = compute_metrics(combined_returns['Portfolio'])
for bench in ['SPY', 'ACWI']:
    if bench in combined_returns.columns:
        metrics_dict[bench] = compute_metrics(combined_returns[bench])

metrics_table = pd.DataFrame(metrics_dict)
print("=" * 70)
print("KEY PORTFOLIO METRICS")
print("=" * 70)
metrics_table

# ============================================================
# 6.2  Rolling Metrics (Sharpe, Volatility)
# ============================================================

fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(16, 14), sharex=True)
fig.patch.set_facecolor('#0e1117')
window = 63  # ~3 months

# Rolling Sharpe
rf_daily = (1 + 0.045) ** (1/252) - 1
for col, color, lw in [('Portfolio', '#00d4aa', 2.5), ('SPY', '#ff6b6b', 1.5)]:
    if col in combined_returns.columns:
        rolling_excess = combined_returns[col] - rf_daily
        rolling_sharpe = rolling_excess.rolling(window).mean() / combined_returns[col].rolling(window).std() * np.sqrt(252)
        axes[0].plot(rolling_sharpe.index, rolling_sharpe, label=col, color=color, linewidth=lw)

axes[0].legend(facecolor='#1a1a2e', edgecolor='white')
axes[0].grid(alpha=0.2)

# Rolling Volatility
for col, color, lw in [('Portfolio', '#00d4aa', 2.5), ('SPY', '#ff6b6b', 1.5)]:
    if col in combined_returns.columns:
        rolling_vol = combined_returns[col].rolling(window).std() * np.sqrt(252) * 100
        axes[1].plot(rolling_vol.index, rolling_vol, label=col, color=color, linewidth=lw)

# ============================================================
# 7.2  Top 5 Drawdown Periods
# ============================================================

def find_drawdown_periods(returns, top_n=5):
    """Find the top N drawdown periods with start, trough, end dates."""
    cum = (1 + returns).cumprod()
    running_max = cum.cummax()
    dd = (cum - running_max) / running_max
    
    periods = []
    in_dd = False
    start = None
    
    for i in range(len(dd)):
        if dd.iloc[i] < 0 and not in_dd:
            start = dd.index[i]
            in_dd = True
        elif dd.iloc[i] == 0 and in_dd:
            period_dd = dd[start:dd.index[i]]
            trough_idx = period_dd.idxmin()
            periods.append({
                'Start': start,
                'Trough': trough_idx,
                'End': dd.index[i],
                'Max DD': period_dd.min(),
                'Duration (days)': (dd.index[i] - start).days,
                'Recovery (days)': (dd.index[i] - trough_idx).days
            })
            in_dd = False
    
    # Handle ongoing drawdown
    if in_dd and start is not None:
        period_dd = dd[start:]
        trough_idx = period_dd.idxmin()
        periods.append({
            'Start': start,
            'Trough': trough_idx,
            'End': 'Ongoing',
            'Max DD': period_dd.min(),
            'Duration (days)': (dd.index[-1] - start).days,
            'Recovery (days)': 'Ongoing'
        })
    
    periods_df = pd.DataFrame(periods).sort_values('Max DD')
    return periods_df.head(top_n)

dd_periods = find_drawdown_periods(combined_returns['Portfolio'])

9. Monte Carlo Simulation VaR & CVaR

Running 10,000 simulated paths over a 252-day (1-year) horizon using bootstrapped daily returns to estimate the probability distribution of portfolio outcomes.

In[17]:
# ============================================================
# 9.1  Monte Carlo Simulation (10,000 paths)
# ============================================================

np.random.seed(42)
n_sims = 10_000
n_days = 252
initial_value = 98_303

# Use portfolio daily returns for simulation
port_ret_array = port_returns.values

# Bootstrap simulation
sim_returns = np.random.choice(port_ret_array, size=(n_sims, n_days), replace=True)
sim_paths = initial_value * np.cumprod(1 + sim_returns, axis=1)

# Final values
final_values = sim_paths[:, -1]

# VaR and CVaR
var_95 = np.percentile(final_values, 5)
var_99 = np.percentile(final_values, 1)
cvar_95 = final_values[final_values <= var_95].mean()
cvar_99 = final_values[final_values <= var_99].mean()
median_val = np.median(final_values)
mean_val = np.mean(final_values)

print("=" * 60)
print("MONTE CARLO SIMULATION RESULTS (1-Year, 10,000 paths)")
print("=" * 60)
print(f"Starting Value:    {initial_value:,.0f}")
print(f"Mean Final Value:  {mean_val:,.0f}  ({(mean_val/initial_value - 1)*100:+.1f}%)")
print(f"Median Final:      {median_val:,.0f}  ({(median_val/initial_value - 1)*100:+.1f}%)")
print(f"95th Percentile:   {np.percentile(final_values, 95):,.0f}")
print(f"5th Percentile:    {np.percentile(final_values, 5):,.0f}")
print(f"\nValue at Risk (95%):  {initial_value - var_95:,.0f} (portfolio falls to {var_95:,.0f})")
print(f"Value at Risk (99%):  {initial_value - var_99:,.0f} (portfolio falls to {var_99:,.0f})")
print(f"CVaR (95%):           {initial_value - cvar_95:,.0f} (avg loss in worst 5%)")
print(f"CVaR (99%):           {initial_value - cvar_99:,.0f} (avg loss in worst 1%)")
print(f"\nProbability of loss:  {(final_values < initial_value).mean()*100:.1f}%")
print(f"Probability of >50% gain: {(final_values > initial_value * 1.5).mean()*100:.1f}%")

11. Factor Exposure Analysis (Fama-French)

Regressing portfolio excess returns against Fama-French 3-factor model:

  • MKT-RF: Market risk premium
  • SMB: Small minus Big (size factor)
  • HML: High minus Low (value factor)

We'll use the Kenneth French data library via pandas-datareader or manual download.

In[21]:
# ============================================================
# 11.1  Fama-French Factor Analysis
# ============================================================

try:
    import pandas_datareader.data as web
    ff_data = web.DataReader('F-F_Research_Data_Factors_daily', 'famafrench',
                             start=start_date, end=end_date)[0]
    ff_data = ff_data / 100  # Convert from percentage
    ff_available = True
    print(" Fama-French data loaded from Kenneth French library")
except Exception as e:
    print(f" Could not load Fama-French data: {e}")
    print("Falling back to market-only factor model using SPY")
    ff_available = False

if ff_available:
    # Align dates
    ff_aligned = ff_data.reindex(port_returns.index).dropna()
    port_aligned = port_returns.reindex(ff_aligned.index).dropna()
    
    # Common dates
    common_idx = port_aligned.index.intersection(ff_aligned.index)
    y = port_aligned.loc[common_idx] - ff_aligned.loc[common_idx, 'RF']
    X = ff_aligned.loc[common_idx, ['Mkt-RF', 'SMB', 'HML']]
    
    # Add constant
    import statsmodels.api as sm
    X_const = sm.add_constant(X)
    model = sm.OLS(y, X_const).fit()
    
    print("\n" + "=" * 70)
    print("FAMA-FRENCH 3-FACTOR REGRESSION RESULTS")
    print("=" * 70)
    print(model.summary().tables[1])
    print(f"\nR-squared: {model.rsquared:.4f}")
    print(f"Alpha (annualised): {model.params['const'] * 252:.2%}")
    print(f"Alpha t-stat: {model.tvalues['const']:.2f}")
    print(f"Market Beta: {model.params['Mkt-RF']:.3f}")
    print(f"SMB Loading: {model.params['SMB']:.3f} ({'Small cap tilt' if model.params['SMB'] > 0.1 else 'Large cap tilt' if model.params['SMB'] < -0.1 else 'Neutral'})")
    print(f"HML Loading: {model.params['HML']:.3f} ({'Value tilt' if model.params['HML'] > 0.1 else 'Growth tilt' if model.params['HML'] < -0.1 else 'Neutral'})")
    
else:
    # Simple market model
    if 'SPY' in returns.columns:
        spy_ret = returns['SPY'].reindex(port_returns.index).dropna()
        common = port_returns.index.intersection(spy_ret.index)
        slope, intercept, r, p, se = stats.linregress(spy_ret.loc[common], port_returns.loc[common])
        print(f"\nSimple Market Model:")
        print(f"Beta: {slope:.3f}")
        print(f"Alpha (annual): {intercept * 252:.2%}")
        print(f"R-squared: {r**2:.4f}")

    w = frontier.iloc[:, i].values.flatten()
    vol = np.sqrt(w @ port.cov.values @ w) * np.sqrt(252)
    min_vols.append(vol)

# ============================================================
# 12.6  Risk Contribution Decomposition (Current Portfolio)
# ============================================================

# Compute risk contribution of current weights
cov_matrix = port.cov.values
w_current = current_w.values

# Marginal risk contribution
port_vol = np.sqrt(w_current @ cov_matrix @ w_current)
marginal_rc = (cov_matrix @ w_current) / port_vol
component_rc = w_current * marginal_rc
pct_rc = component_rc / component_rc.sum() * 100

# Build DataFrame
rc_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Weight (%)': current_w.values * 100,
    'Risk Contribution (%)': pct_rc,
    'Weight/Risk Ratio': (current_w.values * 100) / pct_rc
}, index=current_w.index).sort_values('Risk Contribution (%)', ascending=False)

# Compute total return for each holding
individual_perf = {}
for name, info in holdings.items():
    ticker = info['yf_ticker']
    if ticker in prices.columns:
        p = prices[ticker].dropna()
        if len(p) > 20:
            total_ret = (p.iloc[-1] / p.iloc[0] - 1) * 100
            vol = returns[ticker].dropna().std() * np.sqrt(252) * 100
            sharpe = (returns[ticker].dropna().mean() * 252 - 0.045) / (returns[ticker].dropna().std() * np.sqrt(252)) if returns[ticker].dropna().std() > 0 else 0
            max_dd = ((p / p.cummax()) - 1).min() * 100
            individual_perf[name] = {
                'Total Return (%)': total_ret,
                'Ann. Volatility (%)': vol,
                'Sharpe': sharpe,
                'Max Drawdown (%)': max_dd,
                'Weight (%)': info['weight'],
                'Contribution': total_ret * info['weight'] / 100,
                'Theme': info['theme']
            }

perf_df = pd.DataFrame(individual_perf).T.sort_values('Contribution', ascending=False)

# 4. Correlation risk
if len(corr_matrix) > 1:
    high_corr_pairs = []
    for i in range(len(corr_matrix)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(corr_matrix)):
            if abs(corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]) > 0.7:
                high_corr_pairs.append(
                    (corr_matrix.index[i], corr_matrix.columns[j], corr_matrix.iloc[i, j])
                )
    
    print(f"\n CORRELATION RISK:")
    print(f"  Highly correlated pairs (|| > 0.7): {len(high_corr_pairs)}")
    for t1, t2, rho in sorted(high_corr_pairs, key=lambda x: -abs(x[2]))[:5]:
        n1 = ticker_to_name.get(t1, t1)
        n2 = ticker_to_name.get(t2, t2)
        print(f"    {n1}  {n2}:  = {rho:.2f}")

# 5. Overall risk
